cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.DM 

The paper deals with list decoding of codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also uses techniques from high dimensional probability (cs.DS) and provides improved bounds on list decodability of random linear codes (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the Johnson bound, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CR), and uses a chaining argument, which is a technique in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
